00:32:18,741 --> 00:32:21,209
No reception work.

489
00:32:24,413 --> 00:32:26,529
Hey, wait a minute.
This says Doctor Shirlee.

490
00:32:26,530 --> 00:32:28,645
Right.

491
00:32:28,718 --> 00:32:31,551
The boss wants a doctor,
so that's what you are.

492
00:32:31,621 --> 00:32:33,714
Sign it.
It's not important.

493
00:32:33,789 --> 00:32:36,724
Of course it's important.
It's not true.

494
00:32:38,060 --> 00:32:40,893
Okay, $800 a week.

495
00:32:40,963 --> 00:32:43,591
But it still says Doctor Shirlee.

496
00:32:43,666 --> 00:32:45,657
Listen, listen.

497
00:32:45,735 --> 00:32:48,636
Captain Kangaroo
wasn't really a captain.

498
00:32:48,704 --> 00:32:50,695
He wasn't even a kangaroo.

499
00:32:50,773 --> 00:32:53,537
Besides, no one's ever going to know.

500
00:32:53,609 --> 00:32:56,578
I'm gonna come up with
a first-rate bio for you.

501
00:32:56,646 --> 00:33:00,104
It's just gonna be between
you and me and the lamppost.

502
00:33:00,183 --> 00:33:02,378
In fact, not even the lamppost.

503
00:33:03,953 --> 00:33:08,981
I just don't feel comfortable
pretending to be something I'm not.

504
00:33:09,058 --> 00:33:11,891
If I thought I was doing
a disservice to the public...

505
00:33:11,961 --> 00:33:14,862
I would be the first to say so.

506
00:33:14,931 --> 00:33:17,456
You already went on
the air as a doctor.

507
00:33:17,533 --> 00:33:20,195
If you go on and say,
"I'm not a doctor,"

508
00:33:20,269 --> 00:33:22,260
what are your listeners gonna think?

509
00:33:22,338 --> 00:33:25,364
They're gonna think I'm not a doctor.

510
00:33:26,943 --> 00:33:31,403
Hey, you... you are a doctor...

511
00:33:31,480 --> 00:33:33,414
of the heart.

512
00:33:33,482 --> 00:33:35,416
You're a doctor of the heart.

513
00:33:35,484 --> 00:33:37,543
You help people.

514
00:33:37,620 --> 00:33:39,884
Look at these telegrams.
They love you.

515
00:33:39,956 --> 00:33:42,584
Are you gonna let these people down?

516
00:33:42,658 --> 00:33:45,786
Hmm?

517
00:33:48,231 --> 00:33:50,461
The man's a real ball buster.

518
00:33:50,533 --> 00:33:52,660
That's not a problem for me.

519
00:33:52,735 --> 00:33:54,760
He can be very difficult.

520
00:33:54,837 --> 00:33:58,773
Don't forget.
It's doctor, doctor, doctor.

521
00:33:58,841 --> 00:34:00,707
And also...

522
00:34:00,708 --> 00:34:02,788
Also wear clean underwear
in case I get in a wreck.

523
00:34:02,789 --> 00:34:04,704
Gene, this is...

524
00:34:04,780 --> 00:34:07,943
The woman that saved
that damn shrink spot.

525
00:34:08,017 --> 00:34:10,451
Oh, you've got the real common touch.

526
00:34:10,519 --> 00:34:12,510
I like that, Kendall.

527
00:34:12,588 --> 00:34:14,988
Uh, Kenyon. My mistake.

528
00:34:15,057 --> 00:34:17,457
Uh, but there...

529
00:34:17,526 --> 00:34:21,860
there is a question that I'm afraid
I'm going to have to ask you, Kenyon.

530
00:34:24,734 --> 00:34:28,329
Whatever it is, Mr. Perlman,
you'll get a truthful answer.

531
00:34:28,404 --> 00:34:33,205
Then tell me, how did you
get to be so darn pretty?

532
00:34:36,779 --> 00:34:40,215
I want to publicize
the hell out of her.

533
00:34:40,283 --> 00:34:42,274
Ads, promos, billboards.

534
00:34:42,351 --> 00:34:46,583
Or maybe we should give Shirlee
a little time to settle into it...

535
00:34:46,656 --> 00:34:48,487
and then build an audience.

536
00:34:48,557 --> 00:34:51,993
But that's how we
build an audience, Alan.

537
00:34:52,061 --> 00:34:56,225
Why keep our biggest
potential asset under wraps?

538
00:34:58,301 --> 00:35:01,228
You were fantastic in there.

539
00:35:01,304 --> 00:35:05,798
You played him like a violin.
You're my girl.

540
00:35:05,875 --> 00:35:10,778
I wish Steve could see me now.
Boy, he'd eat his words.

541
00:35:10,846 --> 00:35:12,780
Steve's the ex-husband?

542
00:35:12,848 --> 00:35:15,146
No, Steve's the guy
I was living with...

543
00:35:15,217 --> 00:35:17,481
after the last time
me and Leland got divorced.

544
00:35:17,553 --> 00:35:20,784
The last time?
How many times you been...?

545
00:35:20,856 --> 00:35:23,791
Three times. You've been
married three times?

546
00:35:23,859 --> 00:35:27,158
- Yeah, but to the same guy.
- Oh.

547
00:35:27,229 --> 00:35:30,824
He left, he came back.
We got married, we got divorced.

548
00:35:30,900 --> 00:35:34,233
He got put in jail for shooting
a ready-teller machine.

549
00:35:34,303 --> 00:35:36,703
We got divorced.
It went on and on.

550
00:35:36,772 --> 00:35:39,366
It was such a mess.

551
00:35:49,518 --> 00:35:53,386
You tell no one anything
about your past.

552
00:35:53,456 --> 00:35:56,254
Anything.
I don't want you ever...

553
00:35:56,325 --> 00:35:59,692
Don't talk about your past
at all, to anyone.

554
00:35:59,762 --> 00:36:02,595
No interviews 'til I make up
something right for you.

555
00:36:02,665 --> 00:36:05,964
- Okay?
- Now wait a minute.

556
00:36:06,035 --> 00:36:08,697
I don't think I'm
gonna feel comfortable...

557
00:36:08,771 --> 00:36:11,035
lyin' about who I am
and where I'm from.

558
00:36:11,107 --> 00:36:13,166
You've got a lot to offer...

559
00:36:13,242 --> 00:36:17,008
and I would hate to see
people miss out on it...

560
00:36:17,079 --> 00:36:21,379
because of a few little mistakes you
might have made in your past.

561
00:36:21,450 --> 00:36:23,418
Let me handle your life.

562
00:36:23,486 --> 00:36:26,284
You just go out, live it.

563
00:36:29,258 --> 00:36:31,692
Ohh

564
00:36:34,797 --> 00:36:36,958
Gimme some straight talk,
straight talk

565
00:36:37,032 --> 00:36:39,000
And hold the sugar please

566
00:36:39,068 --> 00:36:41,161
Straight talk, straight talk

567
00:36:41,237 --> 00:36:43,432
Sounds plenty sweet to me

568
00:36:43,506 --> 00:36:47,374
Don't talk to me in circles
in some mumbo-jumbo jive

569
00:36:47,443 --> 00:36:50,640
Gimme just straight talk,
straight talk

570
00:36:50,713 --> 00:36:53,045
And we're gonna be all right

571
00:36:54,984 --> 00:36:56,918
Hi, this is Dr. Shirlee.

572
00:36:56,986 --> 00:36:59,750
What the announcement said,
I really mean.

573
00:36:59,822 --> 00:37:02,882
I'm here to talk about
your problems and concerns.

574
00:37:02,958 --> 00:37:04,949
Anything goes so let's not be shy...

575
00:37:05,027 --> 00:37:06,619
'cause you're among friends.

576
00:37:06,695 --> 00:37:09,926
Our first caller...
Oh, good grief.

577
00:37:09,999 --> 00:37:12,729
Look at me.

578
00:37:12,802 --> 00:37:15,066
What a mess!

579
00:37:15,137 --> 00:37:18,903
I wish this was on TV so you
could see how messy I really am.

580
00:37:18,974 --> 00:37:22,410
I'm busier than a one-legged man
in a butt-kickin' contest.

581
00:37:22,478 --> 00:37:25,914
Straight talk, straight talk

582
00:37:25,981 --> 00:37:28,575
So come on let's talk turkey

583
00:37:28,651 --> 00:37:32,052
Just straight and to the point
about passions, about problems

584
00:37:32,121 --> 00:37:34,316
A bout noses out of joint

585
00:37:34,390 --> 00:37:37,655
Now I want you all to know I care

586
00:37:37,726 --> 00:37:39,921
And I do understand

587
00:37:39,995 --> 00:37:42,862
And hey thanks for lendin' me
an ear out there in radio land

588
00:37:42,932 --> 00:37:45,730
No, Martha, it isn't fair,
but life isn't fair.

589
00:37:45,801 --> 00:37:48,235
Even the Declaration
of Independence...

590
00:37:48,304 --> 00:37:51,239
only guarantees life, liberty
and the pursuit of happiness.

591
00:37:51,307 --> 00:37:53,741
It doesn't say anything about fair.

592
00:37:53,809 --> 00:37:57,336
Doesn't even say you have a right
to be happy, just to pursue it.

593
00:37:57,413 --> 00:38:00,780
But no one
appreciates me and I try to be fair.

594
00:38:00,850 --> 00:38:04,183
Get down off the cross, honey.
Somebody needs the wood.

595
00:38:06,322 --> 00:38:10,452
Straight talk, straight talk
there's nothin' like the truth

596
00:38:10,526 --> 00:38:12,517
Just tell me all your troubles

597
00:38:12,595 --> 00:38:15,155
Pretend I'm Donahue

598
00:38:15,231 --> 00:38:17,426
So don't be shy 'cause we can talk

599
00:38:17,500 --> 00:38:21,197
- Is that for me?
- It's all yours.

600
00:38:21,270 --> 00:38:23,670
I feel like Mary Kay!

601
00:38:23,739 --> 00:38:25,934
Hello, Shirlee here.

602
00:38:26,008 --> 00:38:29,273
Yeah, hi, Dr. Shirlee.

603
00:38:29,345 --> 00:38:32,906
Um, I think I'm falling in love
with a girl at work.

604
00:38:32,982 --> 00:38:35,542
I don't know how to tell her.

605
00:38:41,257 --> 00:38:43,817
You little flirt.

606
00:38:43,893 --> 00:38:46,612
And now Nancy will
continue our week-long

607
00:38:46,613 --> 00:38:49,331
series on talk radio psychologists.

608
00:38:49,398 --> 00:38:53,732
Talk radio psychology. Quick cash,
instant breakfast, minute rice.

609
00:38:53,802 --> 00:38:56,737
The only thing that's getting
slower are traffic and service.

610
00:38:56,805 --> 00:38:59,239
Who's your favorite
talk radio personality?

611
00:38:59,308 --> 00:39:02,709
Dr. Shirlee!

612
00:39:02,778 --> 00:39:05,076
This is not news, in case
anybody's interested.

613
00:39:05,147 --> 00:39:08,116
- You listen to talk radio?
- Only Dr. Shirlee.

614
00:39:08,183 --> 00:39:11,482
The hottest new personality
in Chicago radio is forthright...

615
00:39:11,554 --> 00:39:13,488
she's funny.

616
00:39:13,556 --> 00:39:17,515
Able to solve problems in 30 seconds
and still leave time for commercials.

617
00:39:17,593 --> 00:39:21,256
Hey, pal, you wanna bag that?
I like Dr. Shirlee.

618
00:39:21,330 --> 00:39:25,130
Okay, fine. Who the hell
is Dr. Shirlee anyway?

619
00:39:26,702 --> 00:39:28,363
What's cooking with her?

620
00:39:28,437 --> 00:39:32,897
Although at this time Dr. Shirlee has
refused all requests for an interview...

621
00:39:32,975 --> 00:39:37,878
we do have here in our studio W-N-D-Y
program director Alan Riegert.

622
00:39:37,947 --> 00:39:40,541
Alan, who is Dr. Shirlee?

623
00:39:40,616 --> 00:39:42,584
Who is Dr. Shirlee?

624
00:39:42,651 --> 00:39:46,246
Dr. Shirlee is, and I don't think
it's an exaggeration...

625
00:39:46,322 --> 00:39:51,658
the best thing that's happened to
Chicago since deep-dish pizza.

626
00:39:51,727 --> 00:39:54,821
I think of her as my gift.

627
00:39:54,897 --> 00:39:58,890
I think of her as
my gift to Chicago...

628
00:39:58,968 --> 00:40:02,131
which is the city I love.

629
00:40:02,204 --> 00:40:05,469
Milo, there's a story here.
I know her personally.

630
00:40:05,541 --> 00:40:09,739
- She doesn't know I'm a reporter.
- Doesn't sound like much.

631
00:40:09,812 --> 00:40:12,440
One day she's risking
her neck for 20 bucks...

632
00:40:12,514 --> 00:40:15,574
and the next, she's Chicago's
answer to Dr. Joyce Brothers.

633
00:40:15,651 --> 00:40:18,586
- It smells.
- You're wasting your time.

634
00:40:19,655 --> 00:40:22,055
Don't count on it.

635
00:40:48,183 --> 00:40:51,846
Why are they holding
a cocktail party at the aquarium?

636
00:40:51,920 --> 00:40:56,152
Rich people like to dress up
and be seen in strange places.

637
00:40:56,225 --> 00:40:59,786
I feel like a kid dressed up
in my mama's clothes.

638
00:41:01,330 --> 00:41:03,594
I really don't feel like
I belong here at all.

639
00:41:03,595 --> 00:41:05,858
Ten minutes.

640
00:41:05,934 --> 00:41:08,869
Shake a hand, have a drink,
save a whale.

641
00:41:08,937 --> 00:41:11,201
I'll be with you every second.

642
00:41:18,113 --> 00:41:21,879
Look at you.
Look at you!

643
00:41:21,950 --> 00:41:24,544
I can't get over the transformation.

644
00:41:24,620 --> 00:41:28,716
You look like a million bucks.

645
00:41:28,791 --> 00:41:31,555
You make me very proud
of myself tonight.

646
00:41:31,627 --> 00:41:33,754
You're my discovery.

647
00:41:33,829 --> 00:41:36,730
Alan, I am not the atom.

648
00:41:38,133 --> 00:41:40,567
- How much?
- It's gratis.

649
00:41:40,636 --> 00:41:43,696
I didn't ask what it was.
I asked how much.

650
00:41:43,772 --> 00:41:45,706
It's complimentary.

651
00:41:45,774 --> 00:41:48,902
And it's on the house,
without charge, free.

652
00:41:48,977 --> 00:41:52,071
No kidding?
Well, thank you.

653
00:41:54,116 --> 00:41:56,516
If you don't know
what something means...

654
00:41:56,585 --> 00:41:59,315
pretend you do and follow my lead.

655
00:41:59,388 --> 00:42:02,482
You're supposed to be
a college graduate.

656
00:42:08,897 --> 00:42:10,831
Excuse me.

657
00:42:12,901 --> 00:42:16,393
- Jack Russell, press.
- Invitation?

658
00:42:16,472 --> 00:42:18,571
Our society columnist
is covering the shindig.

659
00:42:18,572 --> 00:42:20,670
Mr. Sindell is already here.

660
00:42:20,743 --> 00:42:23,473
His wife went into labor.
I'm relieving him.

661
00:42:23,545 --> 00:42:25,137
His wife is with him.

662
00:42:25,214 --> 00:42:27,808
His wife is hyperventilating
in the back of a station wagon.

663
00:42:27,883 --> 00:42:30,613
An attractive temp from
the typing pool is with him.

664
00:42:30,686 --> 00:42:35,453
- If you'd like to break the news...
- No, please go in.

665
00:42:35,524 --> 00:42:36,923
Thank you.

666
00:42:43,965 --> 00:42:47,731
- Thinkin' of jumpin' in?
- Not unless you push me.

667
00:42:47,802 --> 00:42:51,738
So this is where you hang out when
you're not dangling from bridges.

668
00:42:51,806 --> 00:42:53,967
Doesn't seem like your kind of party.

669
00:42:54,042 --> 00:42:57,205
I don't want to know what
you think my kind of party is.

670
00:42:57,278 --> 00:42:59,212
Not the stuffed-shirt brigade.

671
00:42:59,280 --> 00:43:01,407
I don't know about you,
but I'm bored.

672
00:43:01,482 --> 00:43:04,781
If you hate being here, why don't
you go somewhere you'd rather be?

673
00:43:04,852 --> 00:43:08,447
I'd rather be with Janice, but thanks
to you, Janice isn't around anymore.

674
00:43:08,523 --> 00:43:12,550
I want you to know I feel
bad about what happened.

675
00:43:12,627 --> 00:43:15,755
No, don't.
You had me pegged right.

676
00:43:15,830 --> 00:43:18,264
My record relationship is 17 weeks.

677
00:43:18,333 --> 00:43:21,700
When you consider it takes longer than
that to grow a good-looking lawn...

678
00:43:21,769 --> 00:43:23,737
it isn't much of a record.

679
00:43:23,805 --> 00:43:25,921
But you keep doing the
same thing over and over.

680
00:43:25,922 --> 00:43:28,037
I guess so.

681
00:43:28,109 --> 00:43:30,543
If a guy keeps wrecking
his car every six months...

682
00:43:30,611 --> 00:43:34,741
you'd begin to wonder about
his driving, wouldn't you?

683
00:43:34,816 --> 00:43:38,946
You're one of those guys that always
has to hold a part of himself back...

684
00:43:39,020 --> 00:43:42,547
always keeping that one cookie
in the cookie jar.

685
00:43:42,623 --> 00:43:44,818
Would you like a little free advice?

686
00:43:44,892 --> 00:43:47,326
It's like you're allergic
to cornflakes...

687
00:43:47,395 --> 00:43:51,331
so you start to buy stuff,
like a can of peas.

688
00:43:51,399 --> 00:43:54,334
You open the can and
inside... cornflakes.

689
00:43:54,402 --> 00:43:57,428
So you pick a TV dinner and...

690
00:43:57,505 --> 00:43:59,166
cornflakes.

691
00:43:59,240 --> 00:44:00,764
What does that mean?

692
00:44:00,842 --> 00:44:04,505
The girls you go out with,
outside they're all different packages.

693
00:44:04,579 --> 00:44:06,012
Inside...

694
00:44:06,080 --> 00:44:09,243
Cornflakes.

695
00:44:09,317 --> 00:44:11,251
So...

696
00:44:11,319 --> 00:44:14,550
- so what do I do?
- Over here.

697
00:44:14,622 --> 00:44:19,184
I have to get out of here.
It was nice to see you again.

698
00:44:19,260 --> 00:44:21,228
Hey, wait a minute!

699
00:44:23,698 --> 00:44:25,632
Hey, wait a minute.

700
00:44:25,700 --> 00:44:29,932
You tell me my life is cornflakes and
cookies, and then you walk away?

701
00:44:30,004 --> 00:44:32,529
- Who are you?
- I'm Dr. Shirlee.

702
00:44:32,607 --> 00:44:35,633
You're a doctor, huh?
What kind of doctor?

703
00:44:35,710 --> 00:44:38,178
I'm a doctor of the heart.

704
00:44:38,246 --> 00:44:40,806
Dr. Shirlee.
You're the radio shrink.

705
00:44:40,882 --> 00:44:45,251
I had no idea Janice was
getting advice from a pro.

706
00:44:45,319 --> 00:44:48,584
Dr. Shirlee, wow.
So, uh, oh...

707
00:44:48,656 --> 00:44:50,590
Um, uh... thanks.

708
00:44:50,658 --> 00:44:53,684
So what do I do?

709
00:44:53,761 --> 00:44:57,094
Maybe you should try datin'
a different kind of woman...

710
00:44:57,165 --> 00:45:01,067
someone whose insides look
better than their outsides.

711
00:45:01,135 --> 00:45:03,968
Someone whose name begins with
"S" and ends with "E"?

712
00:45:04,038 --> 00:45:07,906
- If you know someone named Sylvie.
- No.

713
00:45:07,975 --> 00:45:10,944
- I know a guy named Shane.
- Ask him out.

714
00:45:11,012 --> 00:45:13,503
I'd rather ask you out.
Friday night.

715
00:45:13,581 --> 00:45:15,913
- It's a date.
- It is?

716
00:45:31,866 --> 00:45:34,300
Excuse me. Moritz, hi.

717
00:45:34,368 --> 00:45:36,393
Nice to see you, Jack.

718
00:45:36,471 --> 00:45:41,602
I'll do the best I can, but it's
gonna be a half-hour wait.

719
00:45:41,676 --> 00:45:45,476
- Do you think maybe...
- Dr. Shirlee. Well, well, well.

720
00:45:45,546 --> 00:45:47,980
We're honored to have you here.

721
00:45:48,049 --> 00:45:51,212
We have a beautiful table
for you, right this way.

722
00:45:55,022 --> 00:45:57,047
Medium rare and very well done.

723
00:45:57,124 --> 00:45:59,058
Thank you.

724
00:45:59,126 --> 00:46:02,357
- So you're not from Chicago?
- No, I'm not from Chicago.

725
00:46:02,430 --> 00:46:04,898
Compliments of the house.

726
00:46:04,966 --> 00:46:08,561
- Is it gratis tonight?
- It is for you, Dr. Shirlee.

727
00:46:08,636 --> 00:46:11,104
Just for me?
How come?

728
00:46:11,172 --> 00:46:13,732
Well, because...

729
00:46:13,808 --> 00:46:15,969
because you're Dr. Shirlee.

730
00:46:16,043 --> 00:46:19,444
That's real nice,
but it doesn't seem fair...

731
00:46:19,514 --> 00:46:22,449
for these other people who are
not Dr. Shirlee to be penalized.

732
00:46:22,517 --> 00:46:26,749
I'll pay for a bottle of this
champagne for every table.

733
00:46:26,821 --> 00:46:30,154
This is very expensive champagne.

734
00:46:30,224 --> 00:46:32,590
Money's meant to be spent, right?

735
00:46:32,660 --> 00:46:37,154
What good's it gonna do in
the bottom of my panty drawer?

736
00:46:38,966 --> 00:46:41,434
It's $200 a bottle.

737
00:46:41,502 --> 00:46:44,938
Bad idea. Just forget it.

738
00:46:45,006 --> 00:46:47,839
- Thank you.
- You're welcome, sir.

739
00:46:47,909 --> 00:46:49,934
That's more than
I used to make in a week.

740
00:46:50,011 --> 00:46:53,503
- I thought shrinks were rich.
- Are they?

741
00:46:53,581 --> 00:46:57,312
Not all of them,
at least not at first.

742
00:46:57,385 --> 00:46:59,876
Why would you keep
your money in a drawer?

743
00:46:59,954 --> 00:47:02,479
Aren't you afraid
somebody's gonna steal it?

744
00:47:02,557 --> 00:47:07,017
I figure it's safer in my room
than in a bank these days.

745
00:47:07,094 --> 00:47:09,619
If somebody's gonna steal it...

746
00:47:09,697 --> 00:47:12,097
I'd rather it goes to
somebody that needs it...

747
00:47:12,166 --> 00:47:14,964
than some vice-president
of a savings and loan.

748
00:47:16,904 --> 00:47:18,872
What?

749
00:47:18,940 --> 00:47:21,966
I just... love the way
you look at things.

750
00:47:22,043 --> 00:47:24,375
You're really interested
in me, aren't you?

751
00:47:24,445 --> 00:47:26,572
- Yes, I am.
- That's great.

752
00:47:26,647 --> 00:47:29,878
Most men just want
to talk about themselves.

753
00:47:29,951 --> 00:47:33,819
I want to know everything.
How did you lose your virginity?

754
00:47:37,592 --> 00:47:41,688
You don't want to start with "Where
you from, how long you been in town"?

755
00:47:41,762 --> 00:47:46,222
If you want. Where you from?
How long you been in town?

756
00:47:48,402 --> 00:47:52,270
- Under the bleachers.
- You're from under the bleachers?

757
00:47:52,340 --> 00:47:55,434
No, that's where I lost my virginity.

758
00:47:55,509 --> 00:47:59,377
Our high school had just
lost the state championship...

759
00:47:59,447 --> 00:48:03,474
and my boyfriend,
he was the tight end...

760
00:48:03,551 --> 00:48:06,952
and it was the only way
I could make him feel better.

761
00:48:08,889 --> 00:48:11,289
Who did you lose it to?

762
00:48:11,359 --> 00:48:14,055
- My virginity?
- The state championship.

763
00:48:14,128 --> 00:48:17,757
- To the Lamont Lions.
- Mmm.

764
00:48:17,832 --> 00:48:21,791
How about you?
How'd you lose yours?

765
00:48:22,870 --> 00:48:24,929
How's my star?

766
00:48:25,006 --> 00:48:27,167
I thought I saw you
sitting over here.

767
00:48:27,241 --> 00:48:29,505
I'm not interrupting anything, am I?

768
00:48:29,577 --> 00:48:33,138
Alan, this is my friend Jack.
Jack, this is Alan, my boss.

769
00:48:33,214 --> 00:48:35,876
I don't think of myself
as just your boss.

770
00:48:35,950 --> 00:48:38,919
I prefer to think of myself
as a friend and mentor.

771
00:48:38,986 --> 00:48:41,079
I discovered Shirlee.

772
00:48:41,155 --> 00:48:43,089
You make her sound like penicillin.

773
00:48:43,157 --> 00:48:45,785
Funny guy.

774
00:48:45,860 --> 00:48:48,454
Zim Zimmerman's sitting over there.

775
00:48:48,529 --> 00:48:50,690
I'm gonna get you on his show.

776
00:48:50,765 --> 00:48:53,461
Come over and win
a few points for us.

777
00:48:53,534 --> 00:48:55,968
I thought I wasn't supposed
to give interviews.

778
00:48:56,037 --> 00:48:58,277
Yeah, I thought she wasn't
supposed to give interviews.

779
00:48:58,278 --> 00:48:59,234
How do you know?

780
00:48:59,306 --> 00:49:03,072
I just heard her say so.

781
00:49:03,144 --> 00:49:05,374
Excuse us.

782
00:49:05,446 --> 00:49:09,644
Listen, I told Zim
you'd be a great guest.

783
00:49:09,717 --> 00:49:12,777
I sort of went out on
a limb for you on this.

784
00:49:12,853 --> 00:49:16,482
Don't saw it out from
underneath me please.

785
00:49:29,302 --> 00:49:31,896
Well, this is where I live.

786
00:49:31,972 --> 00:49:36,306
You are full of surprises.

787
00:49:36,376 --> 00:49:40,073
- I had a great time.
- So did I.

788
00:49:40,147 --> 00:49:42,672
In fact, I'm having way too much fun.

789
00:49:42,749 --> 00:49:45,217
What's wrong with that?
It's good, isn't it?

790
00:49:45,285 --> 00:49:47,753
Not for me, Jack.

791
00:49:47,821 --> 00:49:50,688
I have a bad track record with men.

792
00:49:50,757 --> 00:49:54,284
I find men that want to
change me, hurt me, use me...

793
00:49:54,361 --> 00:49:56,795
never just love me.

794
00:49:59,032 --> 00:50:03,696
But what the heck. Records
are made to be broken, right?

795
00:50:21,555 --> 00:50:23,147
We're ready, Dr. Kenyon.

796
00:50:23,223 --> 00:50:26,386
Oh, God.
Okay, here we go.

797
00:50:26,460 --> 00:50:28,428
Now remember...

798
00:50:28,495 --> 00:50:31,191
undergraduate work,
University of Georgia.

799
00:50:31,264 --> 00:50:33,391
Graduate studies,
you went to Stanford.

800
00:50:33,467 --> 00:50:36,664
- You were tops in your class.
- I am not sayin' all that.

801
00:50:36,736 --> 00:50:38,727
I'm not gonna lie.

802
00:50:38,805 --> 00:50:41,638
You want to say you're
qualified to hand out advice...

803
00:50:41,708 --> 00:50:45,144
based on being a three-time
loser dance instructor...

804
00:50:45,212 --> 00:50:48,545
who's never even been near a college?

805
00:50:48,615 --> 00:50:51,049
Okay, you're nervous.
I see that now.

806
00:50:51,117 --> 00:50:53,517
I went over all
the questions with him.

807
00:50:53,587 --> 00:50:55,635
The only way to get
in trouble is if you

808
00:50:55,636 --> 00:50:57,683
deviate from the responses
I've given you...

809
00:50:57,757 --> 00:50:59,737
or he puts down his
clipboard, which means

810
00:50:59,738 --> 00:51:01,716
he'll ask you something
we didn't discuss.

811
00:51:01,795 --> 00:51:04,195
But he assured me
he's not gonna do that.

812
00:51:04,264 --> 00:51:06,755
Which leads me to
the following, Dr. Shirlee.

813
00:51:06,833 --> 00:51:08,926
You're aware of the furor...

814
00:51:09,002 --> 00:51:11,197
You bastard!
You lyin' bastard!

815
00:51:11,271 --> 00:51:15,264
- He said he wasn't gonna do that!
- We're working here!

816
00:51:15,342 --> 00:51:18,038
What do you mean?

817
00:51:18,111 --> 00:51:20,978
Specifically, how it
denigrates a profession...

818
00:51:21,047 --> 00:51:23,777
exploits it for its commercial ends.

819
00:51:23,850 --> 00:51:26,045
Is that what you think?

820
00:51:26,119 --> 00:51:27,984
Have you listened to my program?

821
00:51:28,054 --> 00:51:32,150
Of course I have, but we're not
discussing my opinions here.

822
00:51:32,225 --> 00:51:34,989
Why not?
It's your show.

823
00:51:35,061 --> 00:51:37,495
Let's be straight.

824
00:51:37,564 --> 00:51:39,930
The people you deal with
are total strangers.

825
00:51:40,000 --> 00:51:43,026
You have little or no
knowledge of their history...

826
00:51:43,103 --> 00:51:46,266
and yet you try and solve their
problems in less than five minutes.

827
00:51:46,339 --> 00:51:50,799
Don't you worry that to give advice
with so little information...

828
00:51:50,877 --> 00:51:53,107
can have serious repercussions?

829
00:51:53,179 --> 00:51:55,409
People just give me a holler.

830
00:51:55,482 --> 00:51:58,417
I tell 'em what I think
and hope it helps.

831
00:51:58,485 --> 00:52:01,818
I don't know all the answers.
Do you, Zim?

832
00:52:01,888 --> 00:52:03,515
Don't you think you can hurt?

833
00:52:03,590 --> 00:52:06,184
Don't you worry that
you may give advice...

834
00:52:06,259 --> 00:52:08,250
without enough knowledge
of the person...

835
00:52:08,328 --> 00:52:11,695
I just tell the truth as I see it.

836
00:52:11,765 --> 00:52:14,893
To my knowledge, the truth
has never caused any damage.

837
00:52:14,968 --> 00:52:17,163
Pain sometimes, but not damage.

838
00:52:17,237 --> 00:52:19,535
Very nice.

839
00:52:19,606 --> 00:52:21,540
Very nice.

840
00:52:21,608 --> 00:52:24,805
- Shut him up or get him out of here.
- Sorry.

841
00:52:28,982 --> 00:52:31,644
Let's welcome my special guest...

842
00:52:31,718 --> 00:52:35,552
renowned radio psychiatrist
Dr. David Erdman.

843
00:52:37,857 --> 00:52:40,758
Welcome, Dr. Erdman.

844
00:52:40,827 --> 00:52:43,227
Oh shit! Oh shit!

845
00:52:43,296 --> 00:52:45,355
I'm glad to have a second opinion.

846
00:52:47,434 --> 00:52:49,493
Let's start with...

847
00:52:49,569 --> 00:52:53,335
what are you looking for
in a caller, Dr. Erdman?

848
00:52:53,406 --> 00:52:57,433
I like a caller that fits my listeners'
demographic profile.

849
00:52:57,510 --> 00:53:00,172
I like healthy callers
with healthy problems.

850
00:53:00,246 --> 00:53:03,044
If their questions happen to
tie in with a tape I'm promoting...

851
00:53:03,116 --> 00:53:04,981
so much the better.

852
00:53:05,051 --> 00:53:07,713
No, seriously.

853
00:53:07,787 --> 00:53:10,585
I'm here to help anyone
in my listening audience...

854
00:53:10,657 --> 00:53:14,184
who wants to come to a deeper
understanding of themselves.

855
00:53:14,260 --> 00:53:16,888
- Dr. Shirlee.
- What am I looking for in a caller?

856
00:53:16,963 --> 00:53:19,364
I'm looking for someone
that needs help.

857
00:53:19,365 --> 00:53:21,764
And?

858
00:53:21,835 --> 00:53:24,963
And they have to eat
Froot Loops for breakfast.

859
00:53:25,038 --> 00:53:28,633
And what? Someone with
a problem. Isn't that enough?

860
00:53:31,177 --> 00:53:35,079
Let's proceed with what I feel is the
most interesting part of the program.

861
00:53:35,148 --> 00:53:36,172
Uh-oh.

862
00:53:36,249 --> 00:53:38,240
We have a caller who has a problem.

863
00:53:38,318 --> 00:53:41,617
We're gonna ask each of our doctors
to respond to that problem...

864
00:53:41,688 --> 00:53:43,952
in order to let you see...

865
00:53:44,024 --> 00:53:46,288
the different approaches
to radio psychology.

866
00:53:46,359 --> 00:53:48,520
Oh!

867
00:53:48,595 --> 00:53:50,563
Hi, you're on the air.

868
00:53:50,630 --> 00:53:53,064
- Can you hear me?
- Loud and clear, Joan.

869
00:53:53,133 --> 00:53:57,069
This is Joan. She's 48.
She has a marital problem.

870
00:53:57,137 --> 00:53:59,298
Please doctors,
in the interest of brevity...

871
00:53:59,372 --> 00:54:01,567
keep your responses
to Joan's problem...

872
00:54:01,641 --> 00:54:04,667
down to a minute.
Go ahead, Joan.

873
00:54:04,744 --> 00:54:07,975
My husband's been
having an affair for a year...

874
00:54:08,048 --> 00:54:11,142
and I found out about it
about six months ago.

875
00:54:11,217 --> 00:54:13,879
I asked him to stop, but he won't.

876
00:54:13,953 --> 00:54:16,080
I wrote a letter to
the woman he's seeing...

877
00:54:16,156 --> 00:54:19,148
and asked her not to see him,
but she showed it to him.

878
00:54:19,225 --> 00:54:22,456
Hey, will you get outta there?
What is he doing?

879
00:54:22,529 --> 00:54:27,489
I'm so filled with anger toward him,
I don't know what I'm gonna do.

880
00:54:27,567 --> 00:54:29,660
- Dr. Erdman.
- Hold that shot.

881
00:54:29,736 --> 00:54:34,196
- Joan, do you want a divorce?
- No.

882
00:54:34,274 --> 00:54:37,710
Then I suggest that
you let sleeping dogs lie.

883
00:54:37,777 --> 00:54:40,211
- What!
- You'll have your turn.

884
00:54:40,280 --> 00:54:43,545
Joan, you do not hate your husband
for doing this. You hate yourself.

885
00:54:43,616 --> 00:54:45,846
Give me one.

886
00:54:45,919 --> 00:54:48,217
If you felt better about yourself...

887
00:54:48,288 --> 00:54:51,257
maybe your husband
would want to be with you.

888
00:54:51,324 --> 00:54:53,656
It's her fault
her husband's cheatin'?

889
00:54:53,727 --> 00:54:56,059
I'm simply suggesting
that she look to herself.

890
00:54:56,129 --> 00:54:58,256
Maybe she's too demanding in bed.

891
00:54:58,331 --> 00:55:00,925
You talk to your callers like that?

892
00:55:01,000 --> 00:55:06,199
You should be disbarred or derailed
or whatever they do to doctors.

893
00:55:06,272 --> 00:55:07,864
Derailed?

894
00:55:07,941 --> 00:55:10,876
Where did you receive
your training, Doctor?

895
00:55:10,944 --> 00:55:14,471
- Where did I receive my training?
- Yes.

896
00:55:14,547 --> 00:55:16,714
I'm a graduate of
Harvard, postgraduate

897
00:55:16,715 --> 00:55:18,881
studies at the Sorbonne.
Where did you train?

898
00:55:18,952 --> 00:55:21,682
Where did I train?
I trained at Screw U.

899
00:55:23,690 --> 00:55:28,150
You know who came up with the
expression "Let sleeping dogs lie"?

900
00:55:28,228 --> 00:55:29,661
A dog.

901
00:55:31,531 --> 00:55:34,523
And, Joan, honey, you are
not going to change him.

902
00:55:34,601 --> 00:55:36,865
You gotta live with it or end it.

903
00:55:36,936 --> 00:55:41,305
Tinkle or get off the potty. Either way,
you'll start to like yourself again.

904
00:55:42,942 --> 00:55:46,400
Oh, yes, yes, yes!
Oh, Shirlee!

905
00:55:49,716 --> 00:55:52,708
We love you.!

906
00:55:52,786 --> 00:55:56,415
She was so good!
Oh, God!

907
00:55:56,489 --> 00:56:00,687
- You guys are great.!
- We'll be right back.

908
00:56:00,760 --> 00:56:03,160
This show is fantastic.!

909
00:56:05,865 --> 00:56:09,130
This is great.

910
00:56:09,201 --> 00:56:12,227
She blew both of those guys away.
When can I get the story?

911
00:56:12,304 --> 00:56:15,239
- So now you think it's a story.
- It's a story.

912
00:56:15,307 --> 00:56:18,401
- How much have you got on her?
- Almost enough.

913
00:56:18,477 --> 00:56:20,809
Get on it.

914
00:56:20,880 --> 00:56:22,973
Nail her and fast, huh?

915
00:56:28,587 --> 00:56:31,147
Shirlee, what's the matter?
Where you going?

916
00:56:31,223 --> 00:56:34,681
Let's go back inside.
We didn't say good night to Zim.

917
00:56:34,760 --> 00:56:36,921
Alan, I'm tired.
I want to go.

918
00:56:36,996 --> 00:56:38,930
- You're the pink Mercedes.
- No, I'm not.

919
00:56:38,998 --> 00:56:41,398
No, I'm Shirlee Kenyon.
I drive a pink Mercedes.

920
00:56:45,771 --> 00:56:48,262
- I'm depressed.
- Oh, come on!

921
00:56:48,340 --> 00:56:50,865
What are you talking about?
You should be on cloud nine.

922
00:56:50,943 --> 00:56:52,877
You just buried
those two clowns in there.

923
00:56:52,945 --> 00:56:55,812
That's great, but all
this "doctor" stuff...

924
00:56:55,881 --> 00:56:59,977
and what Zim said about
what if somethin' happened?

925
00:57:00,052 --> 00:57:03,146
Let's face it.
I'm not trained.

926
00:57:03,222 --> 00:57:06,316
Maybe Dr. Erdman is a jerk...

927
00:57:06,392 --> 00:57:09,520
- but at least he's been to school.
- Dr. Erdman!

928
00:57:09,595 --> 00:57:12,928
Dr. Erdman knows about
as much as you do.

929
00:57:12,998 --> 00:57:17,230
I oughta know. He was my shrink
for five years and look how sick I am!

930
00:57:17,303 --> 00:57:19,999
Oh, come on, Shirlee, lighten up!

931
00:57:20,072 --> 00:57:22,199
I'm not a doctor.

932
00:57:22,274 --> 00:57:25,038
And I'm certainly not my Mercedes...

933
00:57:25,111 --> 00:57:27,545
so who am I?

934
00:57:35,321 --> 00:57:37,721
I'm a Cadillac.

935
00:57:39,825 --> 00:57:43,761
Dr. Shirlee, we have Sean on the line.
He's a sober alcoholic.

936
00:57:43,829 --> 00:57:46,627
Shirlee, thanks for taking my call.

937
00:57:46,699 --> 00:57:49,793
I've been sober for two years
and my wife is an alcoholic.

938
00:57:49,869 --> 00:57:52,064
I don't know what to do.

939
00:57:52,138 --> 00:57:55,301
If I stay around her I could drink
again and she doesn't want to quit.

940
00:57:55,374 --> 00:57:58,104
You got kids, Sean, or
is it just the two of you?

941
00:57:58,177 --> 00:58:00,509
It's just us.

942
00:58:00,579 --> 00:58:04,811
In that case, tell her you can't
be with her if she's drinkin'.

943
00:58:04,884 --> 00:58:07,216
If she loves you enough,
she'll try to quit.

944
00:58:07,286 --> 00:58:11,017
If she doesn't, you have to love
yourself enough to walk away.

945
00:58:11,090 --> 00:58:13,115
Like my daddy always said...

946
00:58:13,192 --> 00:58:15,319
a bird and a fish can fall in love...

947
00:58:15,394 --> 00:58:17,794
but where do they make a home?

948
00:58:17,863 --> 00:58:19,888
I saw that!

949
00:58:19,965 --> 00:58:23,025
My helper is makin' faces
at my choice of words.

950
00:58:23,102 --> 00:58:25,969
But what I'm sayin' is true.
Sometimes the only way...

951
00:58:26,038 --> 00:58:30,065
you can get somebody to change
their bad habits is to leave 'em.

952
00:58:30,142 --> 00:58:33,600
And if they don't, at least
one of you's gotten out alive.

953
00:58:38,484 --> 00:58:40,577
What's cookin', Gene?

954
00:58:40,653 --> 00:58:43,247
You made quite an impression
last night, Shirlee...

955
00:58:43,322 --> 00:58:45,586
and not just on Zim Zimmerman.

956
00:58:45,658 --> 00:58:48,718
Mr. Perlman, sometimes
my mouth just runs off...

957
00:58:48,794 --> 00:58:50,989
without checkin' with my brain first.

958
00:58:51,063 --> 00:58:55,625
- I didn't mean to offend him.
- No!

959
00:58:55,701 --> 00:58:58,431
No, Shirlee.
A good impression.

960
00:58:58,504 --> 00:59:00,404
The network called this morning.

961
00:59:00,472 --> 00:59:02,463
They want to take you national.

962
00:59:02,541 --> 00:59:05,908
Promotional tours,
ad campaigns, the works!

963
00:59:05,978 --> 00:59:09,414
Listeners calling Dr. Shirlee
from coast-to-coast.

964
00:59:09,481 --> 00:59:11,881
- How many people's that?
- Millions!

965
00:59:11,951 --> 00:59:15,045
- Millions?
- You've got work, Alan.

966
00:59:15,120 --> 00:59:17,850
I want a photo layout.
"People" magazine.

967
00:59:17,923 --> 00:59:20,585
"Chicago's favorite
doctor at home."

968
00:59:20,659 --> 00:59:23,719
At home?
I don't think...

969
00:59:23,796 --> 00:59:26,390
Don't think, Alan.
Do it! Do it!

970
00:59:26,465 --> 00:59:29,059
Spotlight's on it's shining bright

971
