Living a lie

1018
01:02:35,554 --> 01:02:38,785
Ow! Watch
what you're doin', Jack.

1019
01:02:38,857 --> 01:02:42,418
Just look at me and stop
thinkin' about your feet.

1020
01:02:42,494 --> 01:02:44,928
- Where'd you learn all this?
- I used to teach.

1021
01:02:44,997 --> 01:02:47,261
- Oh, when?
- A long time ago.

1022
01:02:47,332 --> 01:02:49,527
- Where was that?
- What?

1023
01:02:49,601 --> 01:02:52,399
- Where?
- It was before I became a doctor.

1024
01:02:52,471 --> 01:02:55,963
- Loosen up, Jack. Just relax.
- Ohh!

1025
01:02:56,041 --> 01:02:59,067
- Did I ever tell you about my novel?
- No! Did you write a novel?

1026
01:02:59,144 --> 01:03:01,078
I had an idea for a novel.

1027
01:03:01,146 --> 01:03:03,842
I started talking about this book
I was gonna write.

1028
01:03:03,916 --> 01:03:08,478
The guys at the office would say,
"Jack, you started that book yet?"

1029
01:03:08,554 --> 01:03:12,957
One day I got so sick of
saying "no, " I said "yes."

1030
01:03:13,025 --> 01:03:17,052
Then it was, "Jack, how's the book
coming?" "It's coming along."

1031
01:03:17,129 --> 01:03:21,156
Then, "Have you finished
that book yet?"

1032
01:03:21,233 --> 01:03:24,930
One day I just said,
"Yes, it's finished."

1033
01:03:25,003 --> 01:03:28,234
Funny thing was,
I hadn't started it yet.

1034
01:03:28,307 --> 01:03:30,474
I didn't mean to lie.
It just happened.

1035
01:03:30,475 --> 01:03:32,641
What are you tryin' to do?

1036
01:03:32,711 --> 01:03:35,544
What are you tryin' to do?

1037
01:03:35,614 --> 01:03:39,345
The fox-trot, rock step? What?

1038
01:03:39,418 --> 01:03:43,286
- I'm just trying to dance.
- Well, just watch me!

1039
01:03:45,657 --> 01:03:48,285
Rock step, step.
Rock step, step.

1040
01:03:48,360 --> 01:03:50,590
Move those hips.
Move those hips!

1041
01:03:50,662 --> 01:03:54,860
Looking good.
Mmm! Ha!

1042
01:03:59,338 --> 01:04:02,307
I guess nothing like that
ever happened to you, huh?

1043
01:04:02,374 --> 01:04:07,277
- Like happened to me with the book?
- Jack, shut up and dance.

1044
01:04:38,177 --> 01:04:41,271
Outside.! Ball three.

1045
01:04:41,346 --> 01:04:42,904
Nice shot.

1046
01:04:42,981 --> 01:04:46,610
The coach is walking to the mound,
not looking good for the doctor.

1047
01:04:46,685 --> 01:04:49,347
It may be a long trip
back to the bullpen.

1048
01:04:49,421 --> 01:04:51,469
Put your index finger here.
Thumb on the outside.

1049
01:04:51,470 --> 01:04:53,517
Okay.

1050
01:04:53,592 --> 01:04:56,755
She's winding up.
The form is looking good.

1051
01:04:59,331 --> 01:05:02,858
A little high and outside again.
Try again.

1052
01:05:05,737 --> 01:05:09,571
If you ever do write that novel,
what's it gonna be about?

1053
01:05:09,641 --> 01:05:12,235
- That was truly pitiful.
- Why, thank you.

1054
01:05:12,311 --> 01:05:16,645
I don't know. Despair? Greed?
Corruption? All my favorite things.

1055
01:05:16,715 --> 01:05:20,879
Why don't you write about somethin' you
love instead of something you hate?

1056
01:05:20,953 --> 01:05:22,887
- Like what?
- Like baseball.

1057
01:05:22,955 --> 01:05:25,685
Write a book about baseball.

1058
01:05:25,757 --> 01:05:28,817
Just what the world needs,
another baseball novel.

1059
01:05:28,894 --> 01:05:32,591
Sure they do...
if it's great.

1060
01:05:32,664 --> 01:05:35,497
And I bet if you wrote it,
it would be.

1061
01:05:35,567 --> 01:05:38,661
I love when you talk sweet to me.

1062
01:05:38,737 --> 01:05:42,298
- You haven't even heard sweet yet.
- How long do I have to wait?

1063
01:05:42,374 --> 01:05:46,640
- Oh, we're gettin' closer.
- Hey, guys?

1064
01:05:46,712 --> 01:05:48,805
Oops. Game called
on account of cops.

1065
01:05:48,880 --> 01:05:52,976
It's late... and
this ain't no ballpark.

1066
01:05:53,051 --> 01:05:55,178
Can I see some I.D. please?

1067
01:05:55,254 --> 01:05:57,950
- We'll take a rain check, Jack.
- I'll pray for rain.

1068
01:05:58,023 --> 01:06:00,685
- I.D.!
- Thank you, Officer...

1069
01:06:00,759 --> 01:06:04,422
for keeping Chicago safe
from flying lemons.

1070
01:06:04,496 --> 01:06:05,363
Whoop.

1071
01:06:05,364 --> 01:06:06,164
Whoop.

1072
01:06:07,199 --> 01:06:09,190
"Shirlee Kenyon."

1073
01:06:09,267 --> 01:06:11,235
Dr. Shirlee Kenyon?

1074
01:06:11,303 --> 01:06:14,329
It'll work out, Phil.
You call me.

1075
01:06:14,406 --> 01:06:16,567
I will. Thanks!

1076
01:06:16,641 --> 01:06:19,940
Okay. Good night.

1077
01:06:20,012 --> 01:06:22,446
Sorry. Phil's daughter, Carol...

1078
01:06:22,514 --> 01:06:26,541
- ran away twice in the last month.
- Good for her.

1079
01:06:33,625 --> 01:06:36,594
You wanna come up
and check out my carpet samples?

1080
01:06:37,662 --> 01:06:40,529
Is that a line?

1081
01:06:40,599 --> 01:06:43,693
Dusty rose, Christmas green,
or elephant gray?

1082
01:06:45,604 --> 01:06:47,162
Nah!

1083
01:06:47,239 --> 01:06:49,867
- We'll forget about the elephant gray.
- Great apartment.

1084
01:06:49,941 --> 01:06:51,841
Oh, thanks.

1085
01:06:51,910 --> 01:06:54,708
I was worried about takin' it,
paying all this rent and all.

1086
01:06:54,780 --> 01:06:58,147
But Alan says my job's pretty secure.

1087
01:06:58,216 --> 01:07:01,276
It really is great.
The money, the car, this apartment.

1088
01:07:01,353 --> 01:07:04,049
But if my audience
gets tired of me...

1089
01:07:04,122 --> 01:07:06,454
I don't think losin' it
would just kill me.

1090
01:07:08,527 --> 01:07:10,586
So...

1091
01:07:10,662 --> 01:07:14,098
what do we decide? The Dusty
rose or the Christmas green?

1092
01:07:27,779 --> 01:07:30,247
Carpet samples turn you on.

1093
01:07:30,315 --> 01:07:33,807
I tried everything else.

1094
01:07:40,225 --> 01:07:42,145
You probably think you
just heard the doorbell.

1095
01:07:42,146 --> 01:07:43,786
Trust me, you're hallucinating.

1096
01:07:43,862 --> 01:07:47,889
See, most women, right after they kiss
me, tell me they hear a doorbell...

1097
01:07:47,966 --> 01:07:50,400
followed by
the faint scent of orchids.

1098
01:07:50,469 --> 01:07:54,405
- Do you smell the orchids yet?
- No.

1099
01:07:54,473 --> 01:07:57,965
Just the pungent aroma of bullshit.
...

1100
01:07:58,043 --> 01:08:01,535
Wait, wait! No one with any class
shows up unannounced.

1101
01:08:01,613 --> 01:08:04,081
- Ignore it.
- What if it's "The Millionaire"?

1102
01:08:04,149 --> 01:08:06,743
Did you ever see that show
where Michael Anthony...

1103
01:08:06,818 --> 01:08:09,685
shows up with a million dollars
from John Beresford Tipton?

1104
01:08:09,754 --> 01:08:13,315
But there's a catch.
You have to answer the door.

1105
01:08:13,391 --> 01:08:16,292
- Wait, wait, wait.
- Oh, Jack.

1106
01:08:16,361 --> 01:08:18,443
You're a great kisser...
but a million dollars?

1107
01:08:18,444 --> 01:08:20,525
You got a point.

1108
01:08:20,599 --> 01:08:23,500
Stay puckered.

1109
01:08:23,568 --> 01:08:26,867
Coming, Mr. Anthony.

1110
01:08:29,074 --> 01:08:30,871
Hello, baby.

1111
01:08:30,942 --> 01:08:34,241
Surprised to see me?

1112
01:08:36,148 --> 01:08:40,676
Wow, you're doin' very well.

1113
01:08:40,752 --> 01:08:42,686
Very, very well.

1114
01:08:42,754 --> 01:08:44,722
Steve, what are you doin' here?

1115
01:08:44,789 --> 01:08:49,817
I heard you made out, so I thought
I'd come by and see for myself.

1116
01:08:49,895 --> 01:08:53,262
Went by that radio station
and told 'em I was...

1117
01:08:53,331 --> 01:08:57,597
your long-lost brother home from
the Navy just dying to surpr...

1118
01:08:57,669 --> 01:09:00,695
Who the hell is this?

1119
01:09:00,772 --> 01:09:03,536
- I'll leave you two alone.
- No, you don't.

1120
01:09:03,608 --> 01:09:06,406
- Jack, this is Steve. Steve, Jack.
- How you doin'?

1121
01:09:06,478 --> 01:09:10,608
- Don't I know you?
- No! No, I don't think so.

1122
01:09:10,682 --> 01:09:13,014
You never been to Arkansas?

1123
01:09:13,084 --> 01:09:17,020
- We better do this another time.
- Do what another time?

1124
01:09:17,088 --> 01:09:19,386
It's none of your business.

1125
01:09:22,294 --> 01:09:24,228
I don't like your attitude.

1126
01:09:24,296 --> 01:09:27,959
That's a big word for you, attitude.

1127
01:09:28,033 --> 01:09:31,332
Why don't you just
give your mouth a rest?

1128
01:09:31,403 --> 01:09:34,099
Damn you, Steve.!

1129
01:09:34,172 --> 01:09:37,266
Want me to throw him out?
'Cause I'll do it. Ow.

1130
01:09:37,342 --> 01:09:40,106
- I don't like you.
- Oh, really? Too bad.

1131
01:09:40,178 --> 01:09:42,578
I was gonna ask if you want
to spend Thanksgiving together.

1132
01:09:42,579 --> 01:09:44,046
Steve, get out!

1133
01:09:44,115 --> 01:09:46,811
I don't know why you're here...

1134
01:09:46,885 --> 01:09:50,912
or what you think,
but you can forget it, it's over!

1135
01:09:50,989 --> 01:09:54,720
Well, maybe yes and maybe no.
But it'll keep.

1136
01:09:54,793 --> 01:09:56,818
I know you.

1137
01:09:56,895 --> 01:10:00,888
I can't put my finger on it,
but believe me, it'll come to me.

1138
01:10:00,966 --> 01:10:02,490
Tell Shirlee...

1139
01:10:02,567 --> 01:10:05,730
I like the Dusty rose.

1140
01:10:08,873 --> 01:10:11,273
Wait a minute.!

1141
01:10:11,343 --> 01:10:14,176
I do owe you something!

1142
01:10:23,221 --> 01:10:25,849
- Ow.
- Head back, head back.

1143
01:10:25,924 --> 01:10:29,018
- I was gonna kick his ass.
- I know.

1144
01:10:29,094 --> 01:10:33,155
Except I'm really more
of a lover than a fighter.

1145
01:10:33,231 --> 01:10:36,826
I can see that.

1146
01:10:42,340 --> 01:10:45,173
Ow, ow! Now see?
Ow, ow.

1147
01:10:45,243 --> 01:10:48,440
- Maybe we better make it another time.
- Yeah, maybe.

1148
01:10:51,516 --> 01:10:55,350
On the other hand...

1149
01:10:55,420 --> 01:10:58,878
We can... work around it.

1150
01:11:12,137 --> 01:11:15,300
- Want to come in?
- Before I do...

1151
01:11:15,373 --> 01:11:18,467
there's something I should tell you.

1152
01:11:18,543 --> 01:11:20,340
You're gay?

1153
01:11:20,412 --> 01:11:22,346
No.

1154
01:11:23,948 --> 01:11:26,473
- Married?
- No.

1155
01:11:26,551 --> 01:11:28,883
Will it spoil the mood?

1156
01:11:28,953 --> 01:11:31,012
It might.

1157
01:11:31,089 --> 01:11:33,387
Will it keep?

1158
01:11:35,760 --> 01:11:37,819
Yes.

1159
01:12:12,864 --> 01:12:18,097
- Holy moley!
- Is that all you can say?

1160
01:12:18,169 --> 01:12:21,468
Holy moley.!
...

1161
01:12:29,681 --> 01:12:32,081
Holy moley!

1162
01:12:32,150 --> 01:12:34,846
Yeah. Yeah.

1163
01:12:45,930 --> 01:12:49,957
"If I died tomorrow,
I'd go with a smile.

1164
01:12:50,034 --> 01:12:53,094
Meet me at our
coffee shop at noon."

1165
01:12:54,973 --> 01:12:57,601
Couldn't wait 'til noon?

1166
01:13:00,845 --> 01:13:03,075
I just remembered
where I saw that guy.

1167
01:13:04,516 --> 01:13:06,507
I told him it'd come to me.

1168
01:13:06,584 --> 01:13:08,779
Milo?

1169
01:13:08,853 --> 01:13:11,378
Milo, you wanna see me?

1170
01:13:11,456 --> 01:13:15,415
We're putting the weekend edition
to bed. Where's my story?

1171
01:13:15,493 --> 01:13:18,462
- There is no story.
- What do you mean, there's no story?

1172
01:13:18,530 --> 01:13:21,363
Okay, there is a story,
but I'm not writing it.

1173
01:13:21,432 --> 01:13:23,400
Are you going funny on me?

1174
01:13:23,468 --> 01:13:28,371
- Milo, I'm sorry. I just can't do it.
- You know what I think?

1175
01:13:28,439 --> 01:13:32,705
I think maybe you like this Dr. Shirlee
a little too much to tell the truth.

1176
01:13:32,777 --> 01:13:35,746
Is that it?
Let me tell you something.

1177
01:13:35,814 --> 01:13:39,716
A real reporter is somebody who maybe
cries when he writes the story...

1178
01:13:39,784 --> 01:13:43,618
but he writes the story because
the public deserves to know.

1179
01:13:43,688 --> 01:13:45,679
What? What do
they deserve to know?

1180
01:13:45,757 --> 01:13:48,248
Every stupid fact
that comes a reporter's way?

1181
01:13:48,326 --> 01:13:51,056
Maybe sometimes the thing
to do is keep your mouth shut.

1182
01:13:51,129 --> 01:13:54,792
Some facts don't matter to anyone except
the person you're telling them about.

1183
01:13:54,866 --> 01:13:56,993
Don't pull this on me.

1184
01:13:57,068 --> 01:13:59,901
What do you think?
I'm going to admire your backbone?

1185
01:13:59,971 --> 01:14:02,496
You think I'm gonna respect
you for standing up to me?

1186
01:14:02,574 --> 01:14:05,099
Let me tell you something.
I hate backbone!

1187
01:14:05,176 --> 01:14:07,906
I despise people who stand up to me.

1188
01:14:07,979 --> 01:14:10,948
- Please, don't make me fire you.
- You won't have to fire me.

1189
01:14:11,015 --> 01:14:14,746
- Thanks. I'm glad.
- You won't have to fire me...

1190
01:14:15,854 --> 01:14:18,482
because I quit.

1191
01:14:19,958 --> 01:14:23,155
Three's about done,
another fifteen minutes.

1192
01:14:27,632 --> 01:14:31,159
- Hey, hey!
- What were you doin' in Flat River?

1193
01:14:31,236 --> 01:14:33,153
And why were you askin'
questions about me?

1194
01:14:33,154 --> 01:14:35,070
Flat River?

1195
01:14:35,139 --> 01:14:37,539
You talked to Steve.
He told me.

1196
01:14:37,609 --> 01:14:40,169
Give me a chance to explain.
Let's talk about it.

1197
01:14:40,245 --> 01:14:43,806
- All I want is an answer.
- It's not that simple.

1198
01:14:43,881 --> 01:14:45,841
You're a reporter. You
were doin' a story on me.

1199
01:14:45,842 --> 01:14:47,612
No.

1200
01:14:47,685 --> 01:14:51,143
Yes... I was but I'm not.

1201
01:14:51,222 --> 01:14:54,089
That's why you wanted to spend
time with me? Be with me?

1202
01:14:54,158 --> 01:14:57,355
So you could get the dirt on me?
I thought you were different.

1203
01:14:57,428 --> 01:15:00,591
- I thought my luck had finally changed.
- Wait a minute, Shirl.

1204
01:15:00,665 --> 01:15:04,431
- You don't understand.
- You did a good job, Jack.

1205
01:15:04,502 --> 01:15:06,527
They say you shouldn't
take your work to bed.

1206
01:15:06,604 --> 01:15:11,007
- In this case, I guess they were wrong.
- Man!

1207
01:15:11,075 --> 01:15:12,508
Shirlee!

